<br>
TZ and VZ have problems with x teaming and imortal healers, people you can't kill healing the people you can.<br>
<br>
And sullon has HUGE imbalance in teams. Evil pretty much owns everything since they're 90% of the server pop and whatver good or newts did play rerolled evil. But if you're gonna play evil, might as well play on a blue server since it's the same experence. There's no one to PK if you're evil.<br>
<br>
It's close to impossible for any non solo class to lvl up good or neutral right now since there's no one to group with...<br>
<br>
You're prolly better off on RZ actually. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/01 1:16:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=529.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sullon or rallos</span><hr size=1> @#%$ guys dont send a rogue to rallos.<br>
rallos has item loot,<br>
and a huge amount of cheaters useing showeq and various other hacks to make them selves almost untouchable.<br>
and lastly rallos has no real gm support when it comes to these people. I watched a group sit on the walls in nfp and farm PLAYERS for over 4 hours with no trouble from the guides/gms. <br>
if you want to start over on a pvp server I would suggest it be a daoc server to be honest. <p>"PvE in EQ is definately entertaining, enjoyable, and challenging."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/01 9:41:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=529.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://kambic.homestead.com/files/gotwang.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sullon or rallos</span><hr size=1> In all truth, if you want to play real PvP, I suggest a Quake III Arena server =p <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulirintz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lirin TZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/01 9:58:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=529.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/ribbon_small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sullon or rallos</span><hr size=1> UT and CS kick Q3's ass, thxinfola~ <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10458 >Liringlas Lookinglass</a><br>
HWW~ Bard of the 54th Song<br>Fennin Ro<br><a href=http://www.mysticalprophecy.com/>Mystical Prophecy</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/01 11:48:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=529.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://kambic.homestead.com/files/gotwang.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sullon or rallos</span><hr size=1> Personally enjoy the Opera mod for HL, but I don't run a very fast connection so rarely play any FPS game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utheaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Theaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/02 6:06:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=529.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sullon or rallos</span><hr size=1>     I'm a lvl 4 rogue on the rallos, i'm not a twink. i'm an import from the nameless, and i already have a AC8 +5str no drop cloak, and i'll have my reserve tunic tommorow. a rogue can get along just fine on the rallos if he has his game together. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dunkelheit>Dunkelheit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/02 4:34:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=529.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sullon or rallos</span><hr size=1> SZ is for hardcore PvPers.... race war is for bluebies, which like to have the opportunity to PvP sometimes. RZ dunno.<br>
<br>
I can tell you that PvP kann be a pain in the butt... just try to get Jboots in RM as a lighty on VZ and you know what I mean.<br>
<br>
I cannot even imagine how it would be to play on SZ, where every lvl 60 who had a sad day kicks you to hell. Lotta times... with exp loss..... <br>
<br>
have fun <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uclammorsz1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Clammor SZ1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/18/02 2:03:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=529.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sullon or rallos</span><hr size=1> So anyway, lots of people are completely ignorant about SZ and like to flaunt their opinions.<br>
<br>
Here's a quick break down, cuz I care~<br>
Evil Team:<br>
Ruin is the uber guild, yup, they've already started Vulak<br>
Hate is on Giant faction and farming HoT often, just did Zlandi<br>
both the above guilds are in Vel armors<br>
Defilers fall a bit farther below, have a few epics but no Velious armors yet<br>
The rest of the team--PoH/PoF type stuff up to hand of Maestro/Naggy kills<br>
<br>
Neutral Team:<br>
ToW: Newt equiv of Ruin, Mostly (if not all) 55+ with lots of 60's  Full PoG or better Vel armors, ready for Ragefire<br>
SoB: High lvl newts, but there are oh, 12 of them? PoG+ armor as well<br>
Darkenbane/Inkara: Were one and the same until some loot whores did KD w/o the rest of the guild.  Managed to Zerg Woushi with the help of SoB and another lower guild.  Have full PoG gear, a few ToV trinkets, and have been to Seb.<br>
The rest of the team--PoG pharming mebbe, mostly stick to Velious and pharm velks for exp.  Some have made trips to PoH/PoF as well<br>
<br>
Good Team:<br>
Divine Vigilance: Good team super power, farmed Vox til they outleveled her, have done Poh/Pof, some higher lvl Luclin zones.<br>
Sanctus Lumen: Another good team guild with 50+ no clue what they've done...can assume some PoH but the majority of high lvl goods are in DV<br>
rest of the team--lots of moon stuff new guild Black Crown has been hanging out in DL alot<br>
<br>
As for team make up:<br>
player wise: Evil 45-50%<br>
                 Newt 30-35%<br>
                 Good 15-20%<br>
With alts evil is well into the 55%+ range <br>
<br>
I'd say 80% of the player base (total) enjoys pvp...loves to fight.  Approx 20% are here b/c their home blue server has x amount of uber guilds and they wanted a chance to do bigger mobs.  <br>
<br>
Notes: No exp loss from red killers.  If a lvl 60 ganks a lvl 1 (which can happen in non newbie zones) the lvl 1 is simply sent back to his bind point.<br>
For an even con kill loot is coin + an insignia of your targets diety.  Bragging rights for sure.<br>
Lvling is easy...if you are smart about it.  Low population = many empty zones.  Of course, your standard bluebie lvling spots are under constant fire. (OT sf ramp, oasis, MM, CC, BW giant fort, etc).  The 20% increase is nice, lots of people are going to be 60 for the first time here.<br>
People learn their class here or die. I'd love to &quot;duel&quot; people from other servers, after reading their &quot;duel&quot; techniques =)<br>
<br>
Every team can expect griefing from lvl's 1-50.  The goodies that whined about newts/evils griefing them in CB spend time griefing newts/evils in their lower lvl zones.  A lot of people won't CC low greens, we know how it was for us, and it doesn't earn &quot;points&quot; but others spend hours on end one shoting lowbies cuz its funny.<br>
<br>
On a final note, I don't care what team you join, just don't make an SK, too many incapable UBAR 1337 PVP machines already on team evil, I'd way rather you made a rogue =P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utsango.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tsango</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/02 10:41:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=529.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/Recko/fullsize/rocko.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sullon or rallos</span><hr size=1> Sullon Zek owns all!!!<br>
<br>
Any character 5+levels above you con red and CANNOT cause exp loss.<br>
<br>
If they are +5 or -5 levels of you, they con white and CAN cause XP loss and loot their money.<br>
<br>
If they are -5 levels of you, they are green, can cause XP loss, but cannot loot you. (If you die to a greenie tho, you might have to work on your PvP skills.)<br>
<br>
Besides the large scale PvP battles that occur with all different levels fighting each other are fun.<br>
<br>
